  "prompt": "Is it normal to have a dark ring around the iris of my eye?",
  "response": "Yes, it is normal for many people to have a dark ring around the iris of their eye. This ring, known as a limbal ring, is the border where the cornea meets the sclera (the white part of the eye). Having a prominent limbal ring is often considered a sign of youth and ocular health. However, everyone\u2019s eyes are different, and variations in the appearance of the limbal ring are common and usually not a cause for concern. If you notice any sudden changes or have concerns about your eyes, it's best to consult an eye care professional.",
